<p>Community-driven security audits provide several advantages. First, they allow for a wider range of expertise to be utilized, as community members may have specialized knowledge in specific areas of security. Second, involving the community fosters a sense of ownership and responsibility, as users become active participants in safeguarding the Cardano ecosystem. Finally, community-driven security audits promote transparency and trust, as the process becomes more inclusive and open to scrutiny.</p>



