<p>The privacy challenges faced by ADA exchanges and wallets present practical applications for Cardano&#8217;s privacy measures. </p>



<p>As Cardano aims to strike a balance between security and transparency, it is crucial to address the privacy concerns of users when it comes to exchanges and wallets. One of the main challenges is ensuring that sensitive user information, such as transaction history and wallet addresses, remains private and secure. </p>



<p>Additionally, exchanges and wallets need to implement robust security measures to protect against hacks and unauthorized access. Cardano&#8217;s privacy measures, such as its use of encryption and secure protocols, can help address these challenges and provide users with the necessary privacy and security they require.</p>



